Antwarp 15 Aprill 16881
London Henry Collier
S in answer to yd of P. curitt finde that the goods in N. 37 provewell
6 pr Dearer nay more then those of N.36 whower mynsuall
endeavour is not wanting to putt them off as best I can mr. seuthell &
I have been to ghether, & promised to send some new pattarnes, which
I Daylay exspect, when shall send you some to send forward an other
Bale, wee have considdered, & ballanced over & over againe, how to do in the
affaire of T.H. for he apsents him self, my breakes up his housd & remoues
in to the countrey she under the name of I deletter, which is hername
hath imployd m. Southell to procure a vent I say a letter of rent butt
itt is almost desperate, so I see no comng out except wee can yett
him some were or other arrested: I suposed, & do not Doubt by this time
butt that advian De coninck be arrived I shall accept yd 2 bills for
£130: st & that on John vale send for acceptunce & when payd note
accordingly: mr. Southell & I have fuither considdered yd rest ing cloathes
amonghst which there is 5 peeces yeallow cullours which are not to
be sold here for halve the mony, besides one N.9 which is out of a bale
t N.6 for our acctt. in comp. & don you good in the sale of said bale
so consequentsu mij cloth, as you well bee 1678: bought in June & brough
to acctt. of ab following, whoever I never could putt itt off sence & before
the goods should be spoild wee forimd good to returne, them because you
will doubtless beable to make a better price for them in England for the
north contrey, thide, where that cold is still in faskion, they pay nothing
m
here in going out, so you may have y without charges, wherefore have packt
y up in allle HN.1 & shipped aboard Adriaen block for london accordingby
the inclosed, bill of loading & givengd acctt. of sale creditt for the number
of 5 p & you shall allow mee what you shall gett for N.9 in case you do not
approve of what wee don withaut yd order pray write in answer here off
to mr Coots to take out the goods for the ship will be att bruges att least
9 a 10 dayes hence butt mee thinkes I did the best of itt intie for the
cloathes are good & better as those prijses noware, the cullours onely wee
the blaw, yett itt is better to make the best of itt in time then toelate
all the hest I hope to dispose of to good content I must pay this weel
for you £200: which I doubt shall be forceed to redraw & so remaine
In Antwarp 13 Aprill 1681
London Pickeriny & ro brnson
h
S. my last to you was on the 12: curitt to which please to be referred
then send you pattarnes to provide a bale of fine broad cloathes from
the north, which I hope are sent forward by this time now to make
aperfect trijall to see if a generall trade in northren goods shouldrak
desire you please to inorder yd freind to buy a pack of white manchester
bayen 25 peeces & to assort itt from 38s to 48 st a peeces of such
marckes as he shall uudge to be best penny wortless, besides an
other bale to cont. so white kersies 22 yd ned lists of ¼ of ayd
& 3enck broad att least & so white kersies 3oy broaud & fine al bo
red lists so that now you have a desire to provide 3 packes of ilrertes
one with Bayes & one with kersjes which in case care brought
In well, will render to content, butt above all wee want the bests goods
of which when I am well served can dispose of 40„50 some times more
packes in aycare & God be thanked forind hetherto good in corridgment therem
butt all doth depend from well buying in, dressing & ordering, so leave
the rest to you to promote yd owne intrest for when att this side, no
endeavours are wanting to make the best of the goods, allis to be sent to
hull, to be shipt off for ostend or bruges to my order, inclosed you have invoya
of the bale &N. 14 with tijkes cont. 55:p am to ƒ671:8 £111:17:6 which
in case you accept off please to note accordinly in creditt, you haveing bill
of loading also included the ship went from heme this day, butt will
tarry some dayes att gant & bruaes, you please not to mnder valew the goods
for mr. mertens Elkins sold ihis of late 6pence & some a 6 s more then formay
as I have been by acctt. sent to his correspondent here & I am confident they
cost more then what I do send where fore I exspect yd encorrid gement whilst
Ill do all I can to provide the mentioned 130 peeces yett better then any befor
& grest
In Antwerpen 16 Aprill
Anicolaer John Button
mons. volgens gisteren aen ul huysvrouwe hebbe gesoijt sende heden aen ul pr
bode blom maert een pack I.B. daer in 12 stucken serges daer in van de swart
& beste dier te bekomen sijn, den indere soorte soude ul niet gelijken, 4 dese
en can op 2 alder uyterste niet minder geven te betaelen preeus in 3 maenden
permissi gelt als volght
5 serges drapperie 2 mode en 1 grijs a ƒ33:10
2 mode coleure lange breede serges 228 a ƒ 38:10
4 mod. coleure serges van 23 gs a 28:10
3 ditto grijse
comma ƒ 372:18
22 salm
soo de selve ul niet aenstaen, sent se vrijlijck te leyge, want de
goederen noch dierder worden en nouwelijck goet goet opcrijgen is, soo ul
die aenstaen, sal ul een brefken seynde. om te accepteren, heb ae ulhuyste
een van ul brief kens ter handt gestelt soo verwachte de voedoeninge van dander
ter wijle wonters dese weke sal aen maenn, om gelt te hebben de 2 baelen
in wele sijn noch niet gecomen - de advies. wat de selve het minst moeten
gelden want sij moeten geen licenten oft oncosten hier betaelen voor

In Antw. 16 Aprill
Brugge Raphael Coots
mijnh. 14 deser was aen ul mijnen lesten, sedert geene van ul, nochtans had gedacht
den wisselbrief van ƒ4000 soude terugge hebben bekomen den welke dan morgen
tegemoet sien: wegens het pack AT.AN.6 hebbe noch geen advies, als alleen
voor 1MN 2„ met 12 witte perpetuanen, de welke neffens andere tegemoet
sien mr. scawen heeft tot London geladen 5 balen lijnwate aen boort Adriaen
de haes inhoudende jder bale ontrent 800 ellen ongeblijckt vande sleghste
soorte kosten dender bale ontrent £30 st ick wete niet beter of te de selve
sijn in huine matten, als voriger want hij den tijt niet heeft wille afwaghten
die te voederen, ende de winste sijn soo scrap als de on kosten betaelt worden, dat ie
bem oyens weirdich is, soo bidde ul ten arrivemente deselve opt alderminste te
minageeren eghter is geladen aen boort michel Deraes een pack M„N. 119
met ½ roode frisaerden 2 bayen vrappers Dit is gevoyert met ontrent vooelln
witt lijnwaten, wat sijde & cattoene lijnwaert neus doecken ten arrivemente
idde ul voort selve sorge be dragen als voor eijgen & vant gepeirde advies te geven
heb alhier af geladen aen boort Adriaen block eene packie E1N: met £
lakens die terugge sende nae london, soo i. collier ul ordonnerrde die
te ontladen, ul kan sijn ordre volgen
